1
00:00:03,421 --> 00:00:05,507
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,590 --> 00:00:08,218
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,343 --> 00:00:13,389
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,473 --> 00:00:18,520
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:27,028 --> 00:00:31,282
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,366 --> 00:00:35,537
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:39,707
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,293 --> 00:00:48,341
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,424 --> 00:00:51,594
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,554 --> 00:00:54,847
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,931 --> 00:00:57,642
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:02,522
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:07,902
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:07,986 --> 00:01:11,406
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,489 --> 00:01:17,287
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:28,965
DOUBT

17
00:01:38,808 --> 00:01:40,727
You surprised me, Ryuga.

18
00:01:41,477 --> 00:01:43,021
I never thought that you'd
come out and ask me

19
00:01:43,104 --> 00:01:44,606
to play some tennis to get
to know each other.

20
00:01:44,897 --> 00:01:46,232
Is it a problem?

21
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:49,360
Not at all. But did you know

22
00:01:49,444 --> 00:01:50,778
how good I am?

23
00:01:51,779 --> 00:01:53,531
Don't worry, Yagami.

24
00:01:54,324 --> 00:01:57,660
I was once the British Junior Champion.

25
00:01:58,870 --> 00:02:00,997
<i>If I ask him if he's British,</i>

26
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:03,166
<i>is he going to think that I'm trying
to find out more because I'm Kira?</i>

27
00:02:03,875 --> 00:02:05,501
<i>Whatever. I'll give it a try.</i>

28
00:02:06,586 --> 00:02:08,087
Ryuga, were you raised in Britain?

29
00:02:08,796 --> 00:02:11,424
I lived in Britain for five years, but...

30
00:02:11,633 --> 00:02:17,013
Don't worry. There's nothing there
that can reveal L's identity.

31
00:02:17,764 --> 00:02:18,890
<i>Oh, really...</i>

32
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:23,686
So the first to win a set or six games
wins the match. Is that okay?

33
00:02:24,312 --> 00:02:25,313
All right.

34
00:02:32,278 --> 00:02:34,530
<i>This is just a friendly game of tennis.</i>

35
00:02:35,365 --> 00:02:37,742
<i>This isn't a test to determine
if Light is Kira.</i>

36
00:02:39,786 --> 00:02:41,579
<i>But Kira hates to lose.</i>

37
00:02:50,129 --> 00:02:51,381
Fifteen, love.

38
00:02:53,049 --> 00:02:55,968
Hey, hey, Ryuga.
You're serious right from the start!

39
00:02:56,594 --> 00:02:57,762
He who makes the first move wins.

40
00:02:58,971 --> 00:03:00,932
What do you mean that you can't say?

41
00:03:01,265 --> 00:03:02,767
I'm very sorry.

42
00:03:03,559 --> 00:03:04,602
Under L's orders,

43
00:03:04,686 --> 00:03:07,313
no one outside the task force can know,
even you, Deputy Director General.

44
00:03:07,814 --> 00:03:10,733
Even what you are doing and
where you're doing it, huh?

45
00:03:11,234 --> 00:03:12,527
I'm very sorry.

46
00:03:16,614 --> 00:03:17,824
You know, Yagami...

47
00:03:18,324 --> 00:03:22,328
It's been more than four months since
this case has come to light.

48
00:03:23,162 --> 00:03:26,708
People are saying that
the police and L are incompetent...

49
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:28,584
With all due respect, Sir, but...

50
00:03:29,043 --> 00:03:31,087
Can you really call the police
competent for

51
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:32,964
putting their tails between
their legs in fear of Kira?

52
00:03:33,339 --> 00:03:37,510
You should see how many people
are left at task force headquarters!

53
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,637
If you're worried about
what people are saying,

54
00:03:39,721 --> 00:03:41,514
then try not to let them know that

55
00:03:41,597 --> 00:03:45,017
most detectives
have run away from Kira!

56
00:03:47,019 --> 00:03:48,146
Excuse me.

57
00:03:49,731 --> 00:03:50,857
Yagami.

58
00:03:52,358 --> 00:03:55,778
How is L?
Can he be trusted?

59
00:03:57,029 --> 00:03:59,282
I think he's much more
capable than we are.

60
00:04:00,408 --> 00:04:03,369
He's putting his life at
stake right now.

61
00:04:09,041 --> 00:04:11,878
Are they really amateurs?
Who are they?

62
00:04:12,545 --> 00:04:14,589
They're Light Yagami and
Hideki Ryuga.

63
00:04:15,214 --> 00:04:17,884
The ones who entered
this year with top scores.

64
00:04:19,427 --> 00:04:22,555
<i>Don't worry, Yagami.
Kira hates to lose, but...</i>

65
00:04:22,889 --> 00:04:26,058
<i>Most people don't like to lose either.
It's not just Kira.</i>

66
00:04:27,059 --> 00:04:30,062
<i>Is getting worked up and going
for the win something Kira would do?</i>

67
00:04:30,313 --> 00:04:32,273
<i>Even so, if I lose on purpose,</i>

68
00:04:32,482 --> 00:04:35,318
<i>he'll think that getting worked up
and winning is like Kira,</i>

69
00:04:35,401 --> 00:04:38,654
<i>so losing on purpose is
also like Kira... right?</i>

70
00:04:39,739 --> 00:04:41,115
<i>In the end,
it's the same thing.</i>

71
00:04:41,866 --> 00:04:44,786
<i>There's no way that he would
profile me through this tennis game.</i>

72
00:04:45,286 --> 00:04:47,288
<i>He has some other goal in mind.</i>

73
00:04:48,915 --> 00:04:50,249
<i>But even if it is just tennis...</i>

74
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:52,084
<i>I will win!</i>

75
00:04:57,882 --> 00:04:59,926
<i>See? He's trying to win.</i>

76
00:05:00,426 --> 00:05:02,929
Game count, four games all.

77
00:05:04,764 --> 00:05:05,765
All of a sudden...

78
00:05:05,848 --> 00:05:08,351
there's a chair and line umpire!

79
00:05:09,060 --> 00:05:10,061
Sir!

80
00:05:10,937 --> 00:05:13,856
I thought I'd heard of Light Yagami
somewhere, so I looked him up.

81
00:05:14,023 --> 00:05:16,609
It seems he was the Junior High Champion
in 2002 and 2003.

82
00:05:17,193 --> 00:05:19,028
During the Junior High third-year
commendation ceremony...

83
00:05:19,111 --> 00:05:21,113
he announced that he'd only
play in junior high.

84
00:05:21,322 --> 00:05:23,449
He hasn't played in
any tournaments since.

85
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:24,992
Hey, hey!

86
00:05:25,368 --> 00:05:27,453
So what about Ryuga?

87
00:05:27,537 --> 00:05:30,039
He's holding his own with
the junior high champion.

88
00:05:32,542 --> 00:05:36,087
<i>I can read your feelings,
Light Yagami.</i>

89
00:05:36,963 --> 00:05:39,632
<i>As if we'd really get to know each other
by playing tennis.</i>

90
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:41,217
<i>We're just going through
the motions...</i>

91
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,970
<i>Just so we can say
we're better friends.</i>

92
00:05:44,971 --> 00:05:46,889
<i>By playing this match with you,
you'll think...</i>

93
00:05:47,056 --> 00:05:51,394
<i>that I am preparing t0 take a step
closer t0 you.</i>

94
00:05:52,895 --> 00:05:55,147
<i>And then you're gonna try to
get me to say something</i>

95
00:05:55,231 --> 00:05:57,567
<i>only Kira would know.</i>

96
00:05:57,650 --> 00:06:01,737
<i>But you'll tell me you'll need to know
if you can trust me first.</i>

97
00:06:02,154 --> 00:06:05,032
<i>And try to get me to give you details
on the Kira case...</i>

98
00:06:05,992 --> 00:06:07,827
<i>If I want to talk about
the Kira case...</i>

99
00:06:08,286 --> 00:06:11,706
<i>I'm going to have to ask
him for proof</i>

100
00:06:11,789 --> 00:06:15,251
<i>that he's currently in charge of
the Kira Case.</i>

101
00:06:16,168 --> 00:06:19,922
<i>So the first thing you're going to
want out of me is...</i>

102
00:06:20,464 --> 00:06:24,468
<i>proof that you really are L
from a third party.</i>

103
00:06:25,219 --> 00:06:26,262
<i>In other words,</i>

104
00:06:26,679 --> 00:06:28,806
- we'll go to the task force headquarters!
- we'll go to the task force headquarters!

105
00:06:29,599 --> 00:06:32,560
<i>In life, one cannot win
just by playing defense.</i>

106
00:06:33,019 --> 00:06:35,146
<i>To win. ..
You need to attack.</i>

107
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:40,234
Game set. Won by Yagami.

108
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:42,361
Six games to four!

109
00:06:42,653 --> 00:06:44,196
Wow...!

110
00:06:47,783 --> 00:06:50,286
As I expected of you. I lost.

111
00:06:51,037 --> 00:06:53,956
Ryuga, it's been a while since
I've played seriously.

112
00:06:54,874 --> 00:06:56,083
I'm thirsty.

113
00:06:56,334 --> 00:06:58,210
And I have something I want
to ask you,

114
00:06:58,377 --> 00:06:59,795
so do you want to go
get a drink afterwards?

115
00:07:00,421 --> 00:07:04,425
I've lost the game,
so I'll tell you whatever I can.

116
00:07:05,551 --> 00:07:09,096
But before that,
I have something I must tell you.

117
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,431
What is it?

118
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:15,227
Yagami, I suspect that
you may in fact be Kira.

119
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:18,356
If you still want to ask me
knowing that, go ahead.

120
00:07:23,736 --> 00:07:24,737
I'm Kira?

121
00:07:25,404 --> 00:07:27,740
Well, even though I say
I suspect you,

122
00:07:27,823 --> 00:07:28,824
it's only a one-percent possibility.

123
00:07:29,659 --> 00:07:30,701
Leaving that aside,

124
00:07:30,785 --> 00:07:33,037
once I'm sure that you aren't Kira and

125
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:36,290
because you have
sharp reasoning abilities,

126
00:07:36,582 --> 00:07:40,086
I'd like for you to work with me
on this investigation.

127
00:07:43,339 --> 00:07:44,590
<i>One-percent, huh?</i>

128
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:46,425
<i>Nicely worded.</i>

129
00:07:46,968 --> 00:07:49,553
<i>Even if he suspects me
just a little,</i>

130
00:07:49,971 --> 00:07:51,389
<i>it still means that it won't do
any good</i>

131
00:07:51,472 --> 00:07:53,265
<i>if I ask him to meet
someone from the task force.</i>

132
00:07:53,849 --> 00:07:55,977
<i>Which means he beat me
to the punch.</i>

133
00:07:56,769 --> 00:07:57,812
<i>He beat me.</i>

134
00:08:01,357 --> 00:08:03,609
This coffee shop is
one of my favorites.

135
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:07,154
If we sit here, there's no chance
of anyone overhearing us.

136
00:08:08,072 --> 00:08:10,032
Thank you for choosing the perfect place.

137
00:08:10,908 --> 00:08:14,787
We don't have to worry about
how we sit here either.

138
00:08:15,621 --> 00:08:18,457
I have to sit like this.

139
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:23,462
If I sit normally, my reasoning skills
drop by forty percent.

140
00:08:24,338 --> 00:08:26,799
So. . .what did you want to ask me?

141
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:28,384
Oh yeah.

142
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:30,928
That can wait until
you're sure that I'm not Kira.

143
00:08:31,595 --> 00:08:33,389
You can talk about whatever
you want to, Ryuga.

144
00:08:34,807 --> 00:08:40,146
Then excuse me, but do you mind
if I test your reasoning abilities?

145
00:08:41,105 --> 00:08:43,315
Yeah, okay. Sounds like fun.

146
00:08:43,899 --> 00:08:47,278
Then first. . .please take a look at this.

147
00:08:49,989 --> 00:08:54,118
These three are pictures of notes that
we believe were written

148
00:08:54,201 --> 00:08:57,788
by criminals in prison right before they died,
while under Kira's control.

149
00:08:58,497 --> 00:09:01,667
Please tell me what you think.

150
00:09:04,253 --> 00:09:05,296
This is interesting.

151
00:09:06,881 --> 00:09:08,799
<i>Really, this is child's play...</i>

152
00:09:09,675 --> 00:09:12,178
<i>The print number is written on
the back of these photographs.</i>

153
00:09:12,511 --> 00:09:13,846
<i>If I paid no attention to this...</i>

154
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:18,059
<i>And correctly unscrambled
the sentence the way Kira wrote it,</i>

155
00:09:18,059 --> 00:09:20,352
I DO YOU KNOW
GODS OF DEATH

156
00:09:20,352 --> 00:09:20,603
<i>"I do you know,
Gods of Death eat only apples. . . "</i>

157
00:09:20,895 --> 00:09:22,688
<i>There 'd be a strong possibility that
I'd be Kira.</i>

158
00:09:23,939 --> 00:09:28,819
<i>But just because I solve this code
doesn't prove I'm Kira.</i>

159
00:09:31,072 --> 00:09:35,117
It would be amazing if Kira
could not only inflict death on others,

160
00:09:35,201 --> 00:09:36,494
but control his victims'
actions as well.

161
00:09:37,369 --> 00:09:41,749
And there's a message
encoded here taunting you.

162
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:45,920
When we rearrange the messages and
look at the top letters of each line,

163
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:47,379
they form another sentence.

164
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:51,050
Rearranging it into a message
which makes sense would probably be...

165
00:09:51,926 --> 00:09:57,348
I D O Y O U K N O VV GODS
OF DEATH EAT ONLY APPLES

166
00:09:57,723 --> 00:10:00,643
But there are print numbers
in the back...

167
00:10:01,060 --> 00:10:03,187
When we arrange them in that order...

168
00:10:03,646 --> 00:10:08,526
I D O Y O U K N O VV EAT
ONLY APPLES GODS OF DEATH

169
00:10:09,068 --> 00:10:11,320
It doesn't make sense and
it's hard to think that

170
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:13,948
Kira would have wanted you
to read it this way.

171
00:10:14,907 --> 00:10:16,033
Incorrect.

172
00:10:17,701 --> 00:10:19,829
There are actually
four photographs.

173
00:10:20,663 --> 00:10:22,790
When we add this one,
this is what it reads...

174
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:28,504
"L, do you know? Gods of Death who
love apples have red hands."

175
00:10:28,504 --> 00:10:28,921
HAVE RED HANDS

176
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:33,634
<i>It's a fake. I never had a criminal write
this message.</i>

177
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:35,261
<i>Is he stupid?</i>

178
00:10:36,387 --> 00:10:39,723
But even with the three photographs,
my deduction was perfect, wasn't it?

179
00:10:40,099 --> 00:10:41,308
It wasn't perfect.

180
00:10:42,059 --> 00:10:43,769
The truth is that there
are four of them.

181
00:10:43,978 --> 00:10:46,147
It would have been perfect if
you'd figured out there was another.

182
00:10:46,939 --> 00:10:50,276
Yagami, even though you knew
the message wasn't finished,

183
00:10:50,985 --> 00:10:52,444
you decided that there were
only three notes.

184
00:10:52,528 --> 00:10:54,446
You didn't guess
that there was a fourth.

185
00:10:54,947 --> 00:10:56,157
This is also true...

186
00:10:56,782 --> 00:10:57,825
<i>Damn him...</i>

187
00:10:59,243 --> 00:11:01,829
<i>I see. He wasn't just gauging
my reasoning abilities.</i>

188
00:11:01,954 --> 00:11:03,455
<i>He's trying to get me to reveal myself.</i>

189
00:11:03,539 --> 00:11:06,417
<i>If I latch onto this,
I'll play right into his hands.</i>

190
00:11:07,251 --> 00:11:10,212
Hmm. .. I hadn't thought that far.

191
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:14,758
Well, whatever the case, it's not
a message that would lead to Kira.

192
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:16,969
Shinigami don't exist.

193
00:11:17,469 --> 00:11:23,601
Then if you were me, faced with
someone who might be Kira,

194
00:11:23,809 --> 00:11:25,477
how would you check
if he was Kira?

195
00:11:26,395 --> 00:11:28,480
I would try to have him say
something

196
00:11:28,647 --> 00:11:31,650
that wasn't broadcast to the public,
that only Kira would know.

197
00:11:32,651 --> 00:11:34,236
What you were doing just now.

198
00:11:34,862 --> 00:11:36,197
That's amazing.

199
00:11:37,031 --> 00:11:40,201
I've asked several detectives
that same question,

200
00:11:40,451 --> 00:11:43,370
but most of them needed
a few minutes to answer.

201
00:11:43,787 --> 00:11:45,122
And... you immediately thought
of a scenario

202
00:11:45,206 --> 00:11:49,418
in which Kira is talking to the investigator.

203
00:11:51,295 --> 00:11:54,089
Your reasoning abilities are amazing.

204
00:11:56,342 --> 00:12:00,554
The more impressive my answers,
the more of a suspect I become, it seems.

205
00:12:01,263 --> 00:12:03,182
Yes. By about three percent.

206
00:12:04,099 --> 00:12:09,021
But in that respect, it's made me
more determined to work with you.

207
00:12:09,897 --> 00:12:12,816
Even if you are Kira,

208
00:12:13,192 --> 00:12:16,904
I would like for us to work together
on this investigation.

209
00:12:17,696 --> 00:12:19,198
Do you know why?

210
00:12:20,074 --> 00:12:23,827
If I cooperate with you,
the investigation will move forward,

211
00:12:24,286 --> 00:12:26,664
and if I really am Kira,
I might reveal myself.

212
00:12:26,997 --> 00:12:30,542
In other words, conduct the investigation
while investigating me all at once.

213
00:12:31,543 --> 00:12:32,878
I think it's a great idea...

214
00:12:33,963 --> 00:12:36,048
But aren't you getting
the wrong idea, Ryuga?

215
00:12:36,882 --> 00:12:41,095
I'm interested in the Kira case and I
conduct detective work as a hobby, but..

216
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:44,932
I am not' Kira,
and I don't want him to kill me.

217
00:12:45,641 --> 00:12:48,978
First of all, I have no proof
that you aren't Kira, either.

218
00:12:50,062 --> 00:12:53,524
It would be strange forjust
one of us to be investigated, right?

219
00:12:54,024 --> 00:12:56,568
Neither of us have proof
that we aren't Kira.

220
00:12:57,194 --> 00:13:01,573
But Ryuga, if you are L,
I'm sure you can show me proof of that.

221
00:13:02,074 --> 00:13:04,994
Like having someone in the task force
or my father

222
00:13:05,077 --> 00:13:08,122
tell me that you are really L
in person.

223
00:13:08,914 --> 00:13:11,667
If you can't,
I can't investigate with you.

224
00:13:13,252 --> 00:13:15,421
<i>You talk a lot, don't you,
Light Yagami?</i>

225
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:17,756
<i>Typical for someone who hates
to lose.</i>

226
00:13:18,257 --> 00:13:21,593
<i>Seven percent... could he really be...?</i>

227
00:13:23,429 --> 00:13:25,806
I never said that
I wouldn't let you meet anyone

228
00:13:25,889 --> 00:13:27,933
from the task force headquarters.

229
00:13:28,058 --> 00:13:29,018
What?

230
00:13:29,101 --> 00:13:33,605
I am currently working
with your father.

231
00:13:34,773 --> 00:13:39,361
If I take you to headquarters,
you'll help with the investigation.

232
00:13:40,779 --> 00:13:42,364
Am I right in thinking that?

233
00:13:43,949 --> 00:13:45,826
<i>What is he thinking?</i>

234
00:13:49,955 --> 00:13:51,040
Excuse me.

235
00:13:51,415 --> 00:13:52,624
Oh, me too.

236
00:13:54,209 --> 00:13:55,210
Yes?

237
00:13:55,294 --> 00:13:57,171
<i>Ryuzaki, something terrible
has happened!</i>

238
00:13:57,796 --> 00:13:59,340
<i>Light, your father's had a-!</i>

239
00:13:59,882 --> 00:14:00,883
Yagami!

240
00:14:02,092 --> 00:14:04,470
My father had. . .a heart attack!

241
00:14:18,192 --> 00:14:19,526
Well, see you tomorrow.

242
00:14:19,651 --> 00:14:21,403
I'll bring your things that you need.

243
00:14:21,945 --> 00:14:23,781
Light, I leave the rest to you.

244
00:14:24,239 --> 00:14:25,240
Okay.

245
00:14:30,788 --> 00:14:32,748
You're sure it's just fatigue, right?

246
00:14:33,332 --> 00:14:37,878
Yeah. When I collapsed,
I thought it was Kira, but I'm all right.

247
00:14:38,295 --> 00:14:40,964
I've been pushing myself
a bit hard lately.

248
00:14:41,965 --> 00:14:45,636
Especially since your son
has been suspected of being Kira.

249
00:14:46,261 --> 00:14:47,679
You've said that to my father?

250
00:14:48,180 --> 00:14:50,599
Yes, I've told him everything.

251
00:14:51,558 --> 00:14:53,143
Even the fact that I'm L.

252
00:14:55,771 --> 00:14:58,023
That's right. He's L.

253
00:14:58,482 --> 00:15:02,861
We call him Ryuzaki so others
can't find out,

254
00:15:03,153 --> 00:15:04,696
but there's no mistaking it. He is L.

255
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:08,700
<i>He's the real L.
My father says so.</i>

256
00:15:09,118 --> 00:15:12,121
<i>Probably the same L who has
been ordering the NPA until now.</i>

257
00:15:13,247 --> 00:15:15,624
<i>If I get rid of him and
the task force...</i>

258
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,836
<i>No, it's probably not
that simple.</i>

259
00:15:19,753 --> 00:15:23,132
<i>There's no need to rush.
I'll have time to investigate...</i>

260
00:15:24,133 --> 00:15:25,426
<i>At any rate,</i>

261
00:15:25,509 --> 00:15:27,428
<i>I have to be the Light Yagami
who is worried about his father.</i>

262
00:15:28,429 --> 00:15:32,266
So Ryuzaki, has talking
with my son,

263
00:15:32,349 --> 00:15:33,976
cleared away your suspicions?

264
00:15:34,768 --> 00:15:37,563
I'll say that I suspect him,
but it's only a little.

265
00:15:38,605 --> 00:15:40,274
I'll explain once more.

266
00:15:40,816 --> 00:15:44,736
Kira killed twelve FBI agents
who entered Japan.

267
00:15:45,654 --> 00:15:48,866
They were tracking those who
were connected to the Japanese police.

268
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:52,119
One of them was Raye Penber...

269
00:15:52,536 --> 00:15:55,330
There were many suspicious things
surrounding his death.

270
00:15:56,415 --> 00:16:00,502
And I was one of the people
he was investigating.

271
00:16:01,253 --> 00:16:03,172
It's no wonder I'm a suspect.

272
00:16:03,672 --> 00:16:05,674
No, it's as Ryuga says...

273
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:07,801
There is no one else to suspect.

274
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:11,013
Your reasoning skills
are quite impressive.

275
00:16:11,722 --> 00:16:13,515
You're always quick and accurate

276
00:16:14,141 --> 00:16:16,351
Ryuga, I'll cooperate with you
on this investigation.

277
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:20,272
My father has vouched that you're L.

278
00:16:21,273 --> 00:16:25,277
Also, I want to catch Kira
and prove that I'm not him.

279
00:16:25,903 --> 00:16:26,945
Light...

280
00:16:27,863 --> 00:16:31,658
You're going to have to start studying
soon to enter the NPA.

281
00:16:31,992 --> 00:16:34,077
It won't be too late to
do this afterwards.

282
00:16:34,745 --> 00:16:36,246
Dad, what are you talking about?

283
00:16:36,497 --> 00:16:38,373
I don't know how many years
that'll take.

284
00:16:39,625 --> 00:16:44,046
I promised you, didn't I?
If something happened to you...

285
00:16:45,088 --> 00:16:47,216
I'll be the one to
send Kira to his execution...

286
00:16:49,426 --> 00:16:52,221
<i>There's no way that
my son can be Kira.</i>

287
00:16:52,971 --> 00:16:58,227
<i>It's hard to believe this is all an act.
No, if it is an act, it's just way too corny.</i>

288
00:16:59,895 --> 00:17:01,396
Light, listen to me...

289
00:17:02,439 --> 00:17:05,567
The fact of the matter is...
Kira is evil.

290
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:10,113
But recently, I've been thinking
about it in this way...

291
00:17:11,073 --> 00:17:13,909
The real evil is the power
to kill people.

292
00:17:15,202 --> 00:17:18,330
People who gain
that kind of power are unlucky...

293
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:20,749
No matter how you use it,

294
00:17:21,124 --> 00:17:26,421
nothing gained by killing people
can bring true happiness.

295
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:28,924
It's as he says.

296
00:17:29,925 --> 00:17:34,179
If Kira is an ordinary person
who gained this power,

297
00:17:34,721 --> 00:17:36,431
then he is a very unlucky person.

298
00:17:37,558 --> 00:17:39,935
Ryuzaki, I'm sorry for
causing you trouble.

299
00:17:40,102 --> 00:17:42,479
I'll try to get better quickly.

300
00:17:43,063 --> 00:17:44,064
Excuse me...

301
00:17:44,690 --> 00:17:46,692
Visiting hours are now over.

302
00:17:54,366 --> 00:17:55,534
Ryuga.

303
00:17:56,285 --> 00:17:59,913
Is there any way that I can get
you to believe that I'm not Kira?

304
00:18:00,664 --> 00:18:04,918
If you aren't Kira, there wouldn't
be any need to do that.

305
00:18:05,252 --> 00:18:10,591
Cut that out! Think about how
it feels to be accused of being Kira.

306
00:18:13,635 --> 00:18:15,304
It feels horrible.

307
00:18:16,054 --> 00:18:22,519
How about keeping watch over me
in a place without TV or anything for a month?

308
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:27,316
<i>Would someone really go
that far to clear their name?</i>

309
00:18:28,317 --> 00:18:29,192
I can't do that.

310
00:18:29,443 --> 00:18:32,362
I can't do anything which would
deprive you of basic human rights.

311
00:18:32,529 --> 00:18:33,655
And furthermore...

312
00:18:33,739 --> 00:18:36,825
It's nonsense to take suggestions
from a suspect.

313
00:18:37,993 --> 00:18:39,036
I see...

314
00:18:40,537 --> 00:18:41,747
It's all right.

315
00:18:42,664 --> 00:18:45,125
If you aren't Kira, it will become
apparent eventually.

316
00:18:46,001 --> 00:18:48,545
Also, during that exchange
with your father...

317
00:18:49,087 --> 00:18:50,964
I thought that you might not be Kira.

318
00:18:52,174 --> 00:18:54,134
Well then, take good care of your father.

319
00:18:54,926 --> 00:18:56,136
Oh, one more thing.

320
00:18:56,762 --> 00:18:58,513
I said that I would cooperate
with the investigation,

321
00:18:59,056 --> 00:19:02,184
but I don't think I can do anything
until my father is well again.

322
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:04,061
I understand.

323
00:19:04,561 --> 00:19:05,604
Well then...

324
00:19:08,899 --> 00:19:11,401
<i>Hideki Ryuga. . . Ryuzaki...</i>

325
00:19:13,028 --> 00:19:15,322
<i>He's the L I've been fighting.</i>

326
00:19:16,657 --> 00:19:18,116
<i>What is his real name?</i>

327
00:19:20,077 --> 00:19:23,330
<i>Light Yagami. . .are you Kira?</i>

328
00:19:25,957 --> 00:19:26,958
Ryuk...

329
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:30,671
I never once felt unlucky since

330
00:19:31,338 --> 00:19:33,548
I picked up this notebook
and gained this power.

331
00:19:34,549 --> 00:19:38,970
I'm very happy, and

332
00:19:39,054 --> 00:19:41,014
I'll create a wonderful world...

333
00:19:41,890 --> 00:19:43,642
I couldn't care less

334
00:19:43,725 --> 00:19:48,647
if finding the notebook's made
you happy or unlucky.

335
00:19:49,481 --> 00:19:50,565
But...

336
00:19:51,316 --> 00:19:54,111
It seems people who have Shinigami
attached to them

337
00:19:54,236 --> 00:19:55,862
experience nothing but misfortune.

338
00:20:00,075 --> 00:20:03,954
Then I shall show you
an exception to the rule.

339
00:20:05,455 --> 00:20:07,124
I appreciate that.

340
00:20:09,501 --> 00:20:13,255
What is it? Is this the only plan
you can think of?!

341
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:14,506
You think that we'll get ratings

342
00:20:14,715 --> 00:20:18,593
if we do any kind of special program
on Kira, don't you?

343
00:20:19,261 --> 00:20:21,888
We've been getting ratings

344
00:20:21,972 --> 00:20:25,267
because we cover stories that
other stations don't!

345
00:20:25,475 --> 00:20:26,601
Understand?

346
00:20:27,102 --> 00:20:29,521
The problem is with the story.

347
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:31,857
Someone bring me a good story!

348
00:20:32,315 --> 00:20:35,986
But the police are keeping
quiet about this. It's hopeless.

349
00:20:36,445 --> 00:20:40,866
Idiots! If we don't have any stories,
just make something up!

350
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:46,037
Director Demegawa,
a special delivery.

351
00:20:47,038 --> 00:20:48,290
What is this?

352
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:50,709
Who is this from?

353
00:20:56,214 --> 00:21:00,635
This is what I'm talking about.
This is the stuff I want you to come up with...

354
00:21:01,845 --> 00:21:03,764
This is just too good.

355
00:21:04,347 --> 00:21:06,516
"A message to the world from Kira."

356
00:21:07,058 --> 00:21:09,019
"if you don't broadcast this...

357
00:21:09,102 --> 00:21:12,731
"I'll kill you all, starting from
your company's president. .

358
00:21:13,231 --> 00:21:14,649
Who wouldn't air this?

359
00:21:14,983 --> 00:21:18,403
This is amazing,
if it's real.

360
00:21:18,487 --> 00:21:22,491
I'm so happy,
my heart's racing!

361
00:21:23,116 --> 00:21:26,161
TO BE CONTINUED

362
00:21:26,578 --> 00:21:31,500
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

363
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:36,922
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

364
00:21:37,214 --> 00:21:40,509
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

365
00:21:40,592 --> 00:21:45,931
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

366
00:21:46,056 --> 00:21:52,312
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

367
00:21:52,395 --> 00:21:56,900
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

368
00:21:57,692 --> 00:22:02,572
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

369
00:22:02,697 --> 00:22:06,409
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

370
00:22:06,493 --> 00:22:10,038
<i>To accomplish</i>

371
00:22:10,622 --> 00:22:15,252
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

372
00:22:15,335 --> 00:22:20,924
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

373
00:22:21,007 --> 00:22:25,971
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

374
00:22:26,471 --> 00:22:31,810
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

375
00:22:36,106 --> 00:22:37,774
PREVIEW

376
00:22:37,774 --> 00:22:38,525
If I leave things the way they are,

377
00:22:38,608 --> 00:22:41,611
I might be finished within
the next four days.

378
00:22:42,153 --> 00:22:44,656
God is really on my side.

379
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:48,493
Only this time, it's not really God,
but a Shinigami, a God of Death.

380
00:22:48,952 --> 00:22:51,121
NEXT EPISODE: ASSAULT

